getMarshaller

JSourceMarshaller getMarshaller()
Returns the marshaller to rewrite the Java source represented by this.

This method can be called for every JSOM type and the returned marshaller will only rewrite those Java sources represented by the appropriate JSOM type.

traverseAll

void traverseAll(TraverseAction pAction)
Traverses all JSOM members that belong to this and calls the traverseAll() method of these members.

Implementation of this method must perform the following steps in the stated order:

  1. Call pAction.performAction(this).
  2. If an implementation of this interface has any JSOM type members and if pAction.isMemberTraversingEnabled() == true it must traverse these members, i.e. it must call the traverseAll(...) method on these members with pAction as argument, i.e. pAction must be passed through all the members, submembers and so on.
  3. Call pAction.actionPerformed(this).

Parameters:
pAction - An TraverseAction object that provided user defined traverse actions.
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if pAction is null . Because it makes no sense to pass null to this method implementations of this method shouldn't ask if pAction != null for instance. Note that depending on the amount of parsed code that should get traversed this method could be called billions of times and is therefore not a candidate for defensive error handling.
